1) What is a Java package?
A package is a namespace that organizes a set of related classes and interfaces.
Conceptually you can think of packages as being similar to different folders on your computer.

2) What is the CLASSPATH variable all about?
classpath and path are the evironment variables .
usually , you have to put the jdk/bin to path so that u could use java compiler everywhere ,
classpath is the path of your .class files .
the classpath has a default path a period(.) which means the current directory.



